It was really quite cool.

00:01:31.920 --> 00:01:37.800
And when I went to Charlie's, I actually commented
to my assistant that there really are some

00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:40.729
benefits to being blind given that I couldn't
see all the choices.

00:01:40.729 --> 00:01:41.729
So, I didn't actually--.

00:01:41.729 --> 00:01:42.729
[laughter]

00:01:42.729 --> 00:01:47.600
So, as you know, I have been studying choice
now for about 20 years.

00:01:47.600 --> 00:01:53.070
And I essentially look at three big questions--and
those are all covered in the book--which is

00:01:53.070 --> 00:01:55.810
why do we want choice?

00:01:55.810 --> 00:01:59.259
What are some of the things that affect how
